Question 1: When would you want to use a remote repository rathrer than keeping all your work local?

Answer: In case you local becomes lost, stolen, corrupted it's good to have a remote for backups.

Question 2: Why might you want to always pull changes manually rather than having Git automatically stay up-to-date with your remote?

Answer: If more than one person is working on the code, a bug might be introduced, malicious intent might destroy the remote. 
